---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Header from "../../components/Header.astro";
import { FaCheck } from "react-icons/fa6";
import ImageComp from "../../components/ImageComp.astro";
import MarqueeLeft from "../../components/MarqueeLeft.jsx";
import imagesGuimbal from "../../data/imagesGuimbal";
import Breadcrumb from "../../components/Breadcrumb.astro";

const headerData = {
  title: "Our Fleet",
  primaryImage: "/src/assets/guimbal-cabri-g2-flying-over-trees-truflight-highland-park-instrument-rating-helicopter.jpg",
  primaryAlt: "Guimbal Cabri G2 in Dallas, Texas",
};
---

<BaseLayout
  siteTitle="TruFlight Academy Helicopter Fleet | Guimbal Cabri G2 Training Aircraft"
  siteDescription="Explore TruFlight Academy's state-of-the-art helicopter fleet featuring the modern Guimbal Cabri G2. Designed for safety, reliability, and advanced training, our aircraft provide students with a seamless learning experience and prepare them for professional rotorcraft operations in North Texas."
  siteKeywords="helicopter fleet Dallas, Guimbal Cabri G2 Dallas, helicopter training aircraft Texas, helicopter flight school fleet North Texas, modern training helicopters Dallas, rotorcraft training aircraft Texas, helicopter rental Dallas, helicopter flight lessons aircraft Texas, helicopter pilot training fleet North Texas, TruFlight Academy helicopters"
>
  <Header slot="hero" data={headerData} />

  <section>
    <div
      class="mx-auto flex max-w-xl flex-col-reverse items-center gap-10 px-4 py-24 lg:max-w-7xl lg:flex-row lg:gap-10 lg:px-12"
    >
      <div class="flex-1">
        <ImageComp
          src="/src/assets/guimbal-cabri-g2-helicopter-open-doors-truflight-dfw-flight-school.jpg"
          alt="Guimbal Cabri G2 at TruFlight Academy"
          classes="aspect-square rounded-md object-cover"
        />
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-1 flex-col">
        <strong class="text-medium-blue text-primary-500 text-lg font-bold"
          >Guimbal Cabri G2 N522TF</strong
        >
        <h2
          class="text-dark-blue font-display mb-5 text-5xl leading-tight font-bold"
        >
          The Flurry
        </h2>
        <p
          class="text-accent-400 max-w-lg text-sm font-medium tracking-wider lg:text-base/6"
        >
          At TruFlight Academy, we take pride in our state-of-the-art fleet of
          helicopters, designed to provide our students with the best possible
          training experience. Our primary training aircraft is the Guimbal
          Cabri G2, a modern and versatile helicopter known for its safety,
          reliability, and advanced technology.
        </p>

        <ul class="my-3 flex flex-col gap-2 font-bold">
          <li class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <FaCheck className="text-primary-500" />
            AC
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <FaCheck className="text-primary-500" />
            Full glass panel
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <FaCheck className="text-primary-500" />
            Garmin 750TXI and 500HTXI as PFD
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <FaCheck className="text-primary-500" />
            Proprietary engine and system monitoring
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <FaCheck className="text-primary-500" />
            Cargo hook
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p
          class="text-accent-400 max-w-lg text-sm font-medium tracking-wider lg:text-base/6"
        >
          Rental price: $455/hr
        </p>

        <div class="mt-5 flex flex-col items-center gap-5 sm:flex-row">
          <a href="/contact-us" class="btn-secondary">Rent Now</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div
      class="mx-auto flex max-w-xl flex-col-reverse items-center gap-10 px-4 pb-24 lg:max-w-7xl lg:flex-row-reverse lg:gap-10 lg:px-12"
    >
      <div class="flex-1">
        <ImageComp
          src="/src/assets/sling-load-training-truflight-academy-mckinney.webp"
          alt="Guimbal Cabri G2 at TruFlight Academy"
          classes="aspect-square rounded-md object-cover"
        />
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-1 flex-col">
        <strong class="text-medium-blue text-primary-500 text-lg font-bold"
          >Guimbal Cabri G2 N250CR</strong
        >
        <h2
          class="text-dark-blue font-display mb-5 text-5xl leading-tight font-bold"
        >
          Cyclops
        </h2>
        <p
          class="text-accent-400 max-w-lg text-sm font-medium tracking-wider lg:text-base/6"
        >
          We are equipped with not one, but two Guimbal Cabri G2 helicopters,
          renowned for their exceptional safety features, fuel efficiency, and
          low operating costs. The Cabri G2 is an ideal training platform,
          offering a smooth and stable flight experience, making it perfect for
          students of all skill levels.
        </p>

        <ul class="my-3 flex flex-col gap-2 font-bold">
          <li class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <FaCheck className="text-primary-500" />
            iPad mount
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <FaCheck className="text-primary-500" />
            Chin bubble mount
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <FaCheck className="text-primary-500" />
            Full glass panel
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <FaCheck className="text-primary-500" />
            Garmin 650TXI and 500HTXI as PFD
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <FaCheck className="text-primary-500" />
            Proprietary engine and system monitoring
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <FaCheck className="text-primary-500" />
            Cargo hook
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p
          class="text-accent-400 max-w-lg text-sm font-medium tracking-wider lg:text-base/6"
        >
          Rental price: $455/hr
        </p>

        <div class="mt-5 flex flex-col items-center gap-5 sm:flex-row">
          <a href="/contact-us" class="btn-secondary">Rent Now</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div
      class="mx-auto flex max-w-xl flex-col-reverse items-center gap-10 px-4 py-24 lg:max-w-7xl lg:flex-row lg:gap-10 lg:px-12"
    >
      <!-- Image -->
      <div class="flex-1">
        <ImageComp
          src="/src/assets/bell-206-jetranger-helicopter-front-view-truflight-dfw-rotorcraft-training.jpg"
          alt="Bell 206B JetRanger N4237M"
          classes="aspect-square rounded-md object-cover"
        />
      </div>

      <!-- Content -->
      <div class="flex flex-1 flex-col">
        <strong class="text-medium-blue text-primary-500 text-lg font-bold">
          Bell 206B JetRanger N4237M
        </strong>

        <h2
          class="text-dark-blue font-display mb-5 text-5xl leading-tight font-bold"
        >
          JetRanger
        </h2>

        <p
          class="text-accent-400 max-w-lg text-sm font-medium tracking-wider lg:text-base/6"
        >
          The Bell 206B JetRanger is one of the most respected turbine helicopters
          ever built. Known for its smooth handling, mechanical simplicity, and
          proven safety record, the 206B remains a benchmark aircraft for turbine
          transition training and utility operations.
        </p>

        <ul class="my-3 flex flex-col gap-2 font-bold">
          <li class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <FaCheck className="text-primary-500" />
            Rolls-Royce 250-C20B turbine engine
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <FaCheck className="text-primary-500" />
            420 shaft horsepower
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <FaCheck className="text-primary-500" />
            Five-seat cabin configuration
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <FaCheck className="text-primary-500" />
            Cruise speed approximately 112 mph
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <FaCheck className="text-primary-500" />
            Single-engine turbine platform
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <FaCheck className="text-primary-500" />
            Ideal for turbine transition and advanced training
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p
          class="text-accent-400 max-w-lg text-sm font-medium tracking-wider lg:text-base/6"
        >
          Seating: 5 • Engine: 1 • Airworthiness: Normal Category
        </p>

        <div class="mt-5 flex flex-col items-center gap-5 sm:flex-row">
          <a href="/contact-us" class="btn-secondary">Request Availability</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto mb-12 flex max-w-7xl flex-col gap-5 px-4 lg:px-12">
    <h2
      class="font-display text-4xl font-black tracking-wide text-pretty italic sm:text-5xl"
    >
      Why We Choose the Cabri G2
    </h2>

    <p class="tracking-wider text-gray-700 lg:text-lg">
      Our helicopters are what sets us apart from other flight schools. Most
      jobs, outside of flight instruction, will require competence in a turbine
      helicopter. Turbine helicopters cost significantly more to operate, which
      is why training is done in piston helicopters. The Cabri G2 is designed to
      make turbine transition practically seamless. Its full glass panel, its
      engine instrumentation, and its general operating procedures mimic closely
      a turbine helicopter.
    </p>
    <p class="tracking-wider text-gray-700 lg:text-lg">
      Guimbal's Cabri G2 was certified by the FAA in 2015 with transition and
      safety in mind. The other training helicopters available were certified as
      far back as 1938. The newest company (other the Guimbal) certified their
      base helicopter designs in 1979. Why do I mention certification dates?
      It's very hard to certify an aircraft and once certified, the manufacturer
      is forced to abide by all the certification specifications. The Guimbal,
      being certified in 2015, means it has the most up to date materials and
      design on the market.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="flex flex-col gap-10 py-10">
    <MarqueeLeft client:only="react">
      <div class="flex gap-10 px-5">
        {
          imagesGuimbal.map((image) => (
            <ImageComp
              src={image.src}
              alt={image.alt}
              classes="h-48 w-72 lg:h-72 lg:w-96 rounded-lg object-cover"
            />
          ))
        }
      </div>
    </MarqueeLeft>
  </section>
  <Breadcrumb items={[{ name: "Our Story" }]} />
</BaseLayout>
